And what I wondered was whether they were being affected

562
00:22:56,820 --> 00:22:58,820
by the name or the content of the color,

563
00:22:58,820 --> 00:23:01,820
so I decided to do a little experiment.

564
00:23:01,820 --> 00:23:04,820
So I brought these two bottles of nail polish into the laboratory,

565
00:23:04,820 --> 00:23:06,820
and I stripped the labels off.

566
00:23:06,820 --> 00:23:08,820
And I brought women into the laboratory,

567
00:23:08,820 --> 00:23:10,820
and I asked them, "Which one would you pick?"

568
00:23:10,820 --> 00:23:13,820
50 percent of the women accused me of playing a trick,

569
00:23:13,820 --> 00:23:15,820
of putting the same color nail polish

570
00:23:15,820 --> 00:23:17,820
in both those bottles.

571
00:23:17,820 --> 00:23:19,820
(Laughter)

572
00:23:19,820 --> 00:23:23,820
(Applause)

573
00:23:23,820 --> 00:23:26,820
At which point you start to wonder who the trick's really played on.

574
00:23:26,820 --> 00:23:29,820
Now, of the women that could tell them apart,

575
00:23:29,820 --> 00:23:32,820
when the labels were off, they picked "Adorable,"

576
00:23:32,820 --> 00:23:34,820
and when the labels were on,

577
00:23:34,820 --> 00:23:37,820
they picked "Ballet Slippers."

578
00:23:37,820 --> 00:23:39,820
So as far as I can tell,

579
00:23:39,820 --> 00:23:41,820
a rose by any other name

580
00:23:41,820 --> 00:23:43,820
probably does look different

581
00:23:43,820 --> 00:23:46,820
and maybe even smells different.

582
00:23:46,820 --> 00:23:49,820
